title: Avoid duplicate title if bibsys returns the same title for the series as for the issue
message:
Avoid duplicate title if bibsys returns the same title for the series as for the issue

-also testing doc.series.length!=0 instead of doc.series != '' since we
found that doc.series returned from the Ask2 API may be an empty array
instead of an empty string for series objects
-fixed bug where we got no hits searching for e-journals and
e-conferences with avdeling UREAL (removed UREAL-call from url to ask2
because e-resources are centralized)

title: Electronic books belonging to the national library (NB) are available to everyone
message:
Electronic books belonging to the national library (NB) are available to everyone

They are included in the search results even when limiting to bibkode=k,
so we show all e-books as available.

title: More changes to correctly react to book_electronic, journal_electronic and electronic
message:
More changes to correctly react to book_electronic, journal_electronic and electronic

bibsearch.js
-Changed exact match "electronic" to indexOf "electronic" so that the
"how to access"/"where is it "-button reacts correctly to
book_electronic and journal_electronic

bibsearch_init.js
-Changed bookformat-handlebar to react to book_electronic and
journal_electronic
-Added Handlebar-helper ifContains, unlessContains and ifItemType

index.html
Replaced ifCond and unlessCond with ifContains and unlessContains to
check for all types of electronic material

title: Some minor fixes
message:
Some minor fixes

1. Fixed the issue of period that caused the app hang during a search -
solution doublequote the cql
2. Reduced the height of the image howToScanBarCode.png and the font
size to 90% in the how to scan-description-div.

title: Showing another book, if first book is on loan
message:
Showing another book, if first book is on loan

There was a problem where the app would show a book that was on loan
even when there were one or more other books available.

Now the app prefers books that are available over those that are on
loan.

If all books are on loan the first will be shown which will be the
newest.
The preference for the newest books as before is unchanged.
